2. Opp. to approach other foreign and domestic problems—SALT; Middle East;
                    Biol/Chem Warfare; MBFR; Berlin; trade; adjustment of US economy (DOD budgets cut massively); allowing new uses of
                    resources; modernization within DOD, allow
                    catch-up with USSR; prospects to go zero draft;
                    concentrate on such major initiatives as PRC/USSR trips; handle other
                    crises like Mid East and S. Asia; make generation of peace credible.
